    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, AND FENDERS - 5000i, 9000i - ADJUSTMENTS -
        CENTER HOOD GUIDE ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CENTER HOOD GUIDE ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Center Hood Guide Adjustment Side to Side on 9100
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9200
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9400
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA), 9900
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SFA) and 9900
                <emph type="italic">ix</emph>
                (SFA) and 5500
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SFA), 5600
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SBA) and 5900
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                (SFA) with Tilt Hood
            </title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900464">Figure 64</hotlnk>
                for all Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <para>To adjust the center hood guide (Item 1) side to side at the passenger side of the hood to align the
                upper sides of the hood with the sides of the cab, use the following procedure.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly enough to
                    adjust the center hood guide.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen, but do not remove, the two hex bolts (Item 2) that secure the center hood guide
                    (Item 1) to the hood. Adjust the center hood guide side to side on the slotted holes, as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the center hood guide (Item 1) in place and tighten the two hex bolts (Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the hood to the closed position and latch the hood on each side. Check the
                    alignment of the upper sides of the hood with the sides of the cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If further adjustment is required, repeat this procedure.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900464" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G09001D9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
